About the Role

We are seeking a highly skilled Data Scientist to join our team in the credit risk strategy department. As a Data Scientist, you will be responsible for developing and deploying risk management strategies that drive business growth and minimize risk.

The successful candidate will possess strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to work independently and collaboratively as part of a team. They will be responsible for:
• Developing and validating risk management strategies using advanced data analytics and domain expertise;
• Extracting and exploring data, validating data integrity, performing ad hoc analysis, and evaluating new data sources for usage in strategy development;
• Maintaining robust documentation of approach and techniques used, including objectives, assumptions, performance, weaknesses, and limitations;
• Adapting to new tools, libraries, technologies, and platforms as needed;
• Partnering with engineers to validate and deploy scalable solutions;
• Collaborating to gather insight from partners across the organization;
• Further developing expertise in data science and engineering through self-study, project exposure, and guidance from senior team members;

The ideal candidate will have a degree in a quantitative field and at least 3 years of experience in Data Science. They will also have experience building and implementing risk strategies in production, a deep understanding of segmentation techniques such as decision trees, and proficiency in Python and SQL.

Key Requirements

To be successful in this role, you will need to bring the following skills and qualifications:
• A degree in a quantitative field;
• At least 3 years of Data Science experience;
• Experience building and implementing risk strategies in production;
• A deep understanding of segmentation techniques such as decision trees;
• Proficiency in Python and SQL;
• Practical experience using Spark is a plus;
• Understanding of statistical modeling techniques is a plus;
• Technical understanding of algorithm complexity, probability, and statistics;
• Self-driven with an aptitude for independent research and problem-solving;
• Ability to multi-task in a fast-paced environment.

